#6656

Create a.scss:

``` scss
:root {
  --css-var: red;
}
```

Create b.scss:

``` scss
@import "a";

a {
  background-color: var(--css-var);
}
```

Go to definition on `--css-var` doesn't work.

While testing https://github.com/Microsoft/vscode/issues/6248:
- VSCode Version: 1.1.0 alpha
- OS Version: OS X 10

Steps to Reproduce:
- create the simple CS Code extension (TypeScript)
- use this code in the sample extension:

  ``` ts
      let launchConfig = {
          "name": "FakeNode",
          "type": "node",
          "request": "launch",
          "program": "${workspaceRoot}/test.js",
          "cwd": "${workspaceRoot}",
          "stopOnEntry": true
      };

      vscode.commands.executeCommand('vscode.startDebug', launchConfig).then(() => {
          vscode.window.showInformationMessage('OK!');
      }, err => {
          vscode.window.showInformationMessage('Error: ' + err.message);
      });
  ```
- press F5
- in the new VS Code window create and open a new workspace
- create a file test.js with this contents:

  ``` ts
     console.log("hello world");
  ```
- trigger the 'Hello' action

Observe:
this error shows up:
![2016-05-24 15-46-22](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1898161/15506141/bb77dec8-21c6-11e6-9a4e-b4247af257fc.png)
- Now create a launch config for debug type 'node.js'.

Observe:
Debugging starts successfully.

Starting a debug session programmatically should not require to have a launch config file in the workspace.
